"{\"uid\": \"washingtonexaminer.com-news-2967867-paris-2024-torch-relay-from-greece-underway-after-lighting-in-ancient-olympia\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Therelayfor the torch of the 2024ParisOlympic Gamesfrom Greece toFranceis underway after it was lit in ancientOlympiaon Tuesday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 62, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9988945177089978, \"rank\": 0.000703086144328988, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lighting of the torch took place during a traditional ceremony in which Mary Mina, a Greek actress, took the role of the\\u00a0high priestess and ignited the torch with a backup flame,accordingto a report.\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6812949273973038, \"rank\": 0.4094860755491339, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 219, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8996445884303367, \"rank\": 0.08795333031470232, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditionally, a parabolic mirror\\u00a0is used, but the backup flame was employed due to cloudy skies.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch will now travel on a 68-day relay before it arrives in the French capital, where it will set ablaze the Olympic Flame and signal the start of the Olympic Games on July 26, the report noted.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9489028586433275, \"rank\": 0.05107127790168797, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Flame\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greek Olympic rowing champion Stefanos Ntouskos is the first runner in the relay, and he will hand off the flame to three-time French Olympic medalist and swimmer Laure Manaudou, who serves as the representative of the host city.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8996445884303367, \"rank\": 0.08795333031470232, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}, {\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9489028586433275, \"rank\": 0.05107127790168797, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, 